  "prompt": "How do I convert .qsv files to .MP4?",
  "response": "To convert .qsv files to .MP4, you can use several methods:\n\n1. Using FFmpeg (free, command-line):\n- Download FFmpeg from ffmpeg.org\n- Open command prompt\n- Use this command:\n```\nffmpeg -i input.qsv -c copy output.mp4\n```\n\n2. Handbrake (free, user-friendly):\n- Download Handbrake\n- Open the program\n- Select .qsv file\n- Choose MP4 as output format\n- Start conversion\n\n3. VLC Media Player:\n- Open VLC\n- Media > Convert/Save\n- Add .qsv file\n- Choose MP4 as output profile\n- Convert\n\n4. Online converters:\n- Websites like Zamzar or CloudConvert\n- Upload .qsv file\n- Select MP4 as output\n- Download converted file\n\n5. Sony Vegas Pro (if you have it):\n- Import .qsv file\n- Export/Render as MP4\n\nPro Tips:\n- Ensure you have enough storage space\n- Conversion quality depends on source file\n- Faster methods use direct stream copying\n\nChoose the method that best suits your technical skill and available resources.",
